**Attack Payload**:
```bash
# Attacker from tenant 1 accessing tenant 2's customer
curl -H "Authorization: Bearer <tenant_1_token>" \
     "https://api.example.com/customers/5001"
# Returns customer 5001 even if they belong to tenant 2

# Enumerate all tenants' data by manipulating query param
curl -H "Authorization: Bearer <tenant_1_token>" \
     "https://api.example.com/customers?tenant_id=2"
# Returns all customers from tenant 2
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Customer lookup ignores tenant context entirely - any valid customer ID returns data regardless of tenant ownership
- List endpoint accepts tenant_id from user-controlled query parameter instead of authenticated session
- Allows complete enumeration of competitor/other organization data including PII (SSN, email)
- Single IDOR can expose entire multi-tenant database

